HEADWORD: Ligustrin
<hw>Li*gus"trin</hw> <pr>(l⟦isl⟧*g⟦ucr⟧s"tr⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter principle found in the bark of the
privet <spn>(Ligustrum vulgare)</spn>, and extracted as a white
crystalline substance with a warm, bitter taste; -- called also
<altname>ligustron</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Likable</ent>⟦br⟧
